        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 4 at 1:20PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 120 PM MDT, Trained spotters reported a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from near Albuquerque to near Sandia
Heights, moving north at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Trained spotters reported.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Albuquerque, Rio Rancho, Bernalillo, Corrales, Los Ranchos De
Albuquerque, North Valley, Sandia Pueblo, Sandia Heights, Rio
Rancho Intel Area and Vista Hills.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 40 between Mile Markers 157 and 167.
Highway 550 between Mile Markers 1 and 3.
Interstate 25 between Mile Markers 222 and 247.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
